44
00:02:41,936 --> 00:02:44,536
And if you're experienced, you
might be wondering, signing.


45
00:02:44,876 --> 00:02:45,786
How does it work?


46
00:02:45,966 --> 00:02:47,906
Well, we use this codesign tool.


47
00:02:48,356 --> 00:02:51,766
And what codesign does is,
it takes your app's bundle


48
00:02:51,956 --> 00:02:53,786
and applies a code seal.


49
00:02:54,566 --> 00:02:57,336
And this allows the
system to detect changes


50
00:02:57,336 --> 00:03:00,466
that have been made after
the app has been signed.


51
00:03:01,676 --> 00:03:06,046
So if someone messes with your
app, it won't install or launch.


52
00:03:07,296 --> 00:03:12,026
Codesign also applies a code
signature to the application.


53
00:03:12,336 --> 00:03:13,976
So it can be identified.


54
00:03:14,146 --> 00:03:17,066
And people know where
the app came from.


55
00:03:20,136 --> 00:03:24,096
There are three things that you
need in order to sign your apps.


56
00:03:24,886 --> 00:03:27,386
The first thing is a
signing certificate.


57
00:03:27,716 --> 00:03:31,786
Signing certificates establish
your identity as a developer.


58
00:03:33,156 --> 00:03:36,376
Provisioning profiles
are all about your apps,


59
00:03:36,556 --> 00:03:37,846
and they grant permissions.


60
00:03:38,466 --> 00:03:43,136
And entitlements declare
support for capabilities.


61
00:03:43,336 --> 00:03:44,876
Like iCloud or Wallet.


62
00:03:46,676 --> 00:03:48,006
So certificates.


63
00:03:48,526 --> 00:03:50,206
These are issued by Apple.


64
00:03:50,556 --> 00:03:53,946
And this is important because
the device needs a trust chain


65
00:03:53,946 --> 00:03:57,206
back to Apple so it
can install the app.


66
00:03:58,016 --> 00:04:00,526
And certificates
come in two forms.


67
00:04:00,916 --> 00:04:02,666
You have development
certificates,


68
00:04:03,396 --> 00:04:04,626
which are for build and run.


69
00:04:05,026 --> 00:04:07,216
And you have distribution
certificates.


70
00:04:07,586 --> 00:04:08,466
Which are used


71
00:04:08,566 --> 00:04:10,716
for authentication
with iTunes Connect.


72
00:04:11,296 --> 00:04:14,296
Or, if these are
enterprise certificates,


73
00:04:14,466 --> 00:04:16,435
it's for distribution to users.


74
00:04:18,296 --> 00:04:22,466
And all signing certificates
require a private key.


75
00:04:22,906 --> 00:04:25,556
This private key has
to be in the keychain


76
00:04:25,716 --> 00:04:28,026
if you want to sign your apps.


77
00:04:28,206 --> 00:04:31,446
And the private key for
a certificate is created


78
00:04:31,446 --> 00:04:33,276
when the certificate
gets generated.


79
00:04:33,276 --> 00:04:36,206
And so it's very important
to have this private key.


80
00:04:37,486 --> 00:04:38,836
And it's worth noting here


81
00:04:38,836 --> 00:04:42,056
that Apple never has a
copy of your private keys.


82
00:04:42,196 --> 00:04:45,036
You can't go to the developer
website and download them.


83
00:04:45,536 --> 00:04:49,216
Now the good news
is, in Xcode 8,


84
00:04:49,396 --> 00:04:51,836
for your development
certificates, you don't need


85
00:04:51,836 --> 00:04:53,066
to worry about this anymore.


86
00:04:53,186 --> 00:04:57,106
And we'll talk more
about that in a second.


87
00:04:57,226 --> 00:05:00,176
Provisioning profiles
are also issued by Apple.


88
00:05:00,666 --> 00:05:03,646
And in contrast to
certificates which are all


89
00:05:03,646 --> 00:05:05,616
about your identity
as a developer,


90
00:05:06,056 --> 00:05:08,826
the profiles are
all about your apps.


91
00:05:10,956 --> 00:05:14,856
Profiles allow access to
things like running on devices.


92
00:05:15,356 --> 00:05:18,396
There's a list of
identifiers in a profile.


93
00:05:18,526 --> 00:05:22,156
And at install time, the
device runs down those list


94
00:05:22,156 --> 00:05:24,936
of identifiers to check
if yours is included.


95
00:05:25,176 --> 00:05:28,006
And if it is, you
can install the app.


96
00:05:28,896 --> 00:05:33,066
Profiles also allow
access to entitlements.


97
00:05:33,506 --> 00:05:36,406
There's a white list of
entitlements in a profile.


98
00:05:36,786 --> 00:05:38,436
And if you want to
use an entitlement,


99
00:05:38,606 --> 00:05:40,416
it has to be in that list.


100
00:05:41,436 --> 00:05:43,116
Now once again, if you're new,


101
00:05:43,276 --> 00:05:44,666
you don't need to
think about this.


102
00:05:44,666 --> 00:05:46,296
Xcode handles this for you.


103
00:05:46,646 --> 00:05:48,196
And if you're experienced,


104
00:05:48,396 --> 00:05:51,366
you might be wondering
why you need a new profile


105
00:05:51,516 --> 00:05:54,246
when you add an entitlement
to your app.


106
00:05:54,406 --> 00:05:57,186
It's because of that white list.


107
00:05:57,816 --> 00:05:59,256
Speaking of entitlements,


108
00:05:59,936 --> 00:06:02,766
entitlements declare
support for capabilities.


109
00:06:03,566 --> 00:06:06,826
And fundamentally an
entitlement is just a string


110
00:06:07,326 --> 00:06:08,826
with an associated value.


111
00:06:08,996 --> 00:06:10,206
Like a string or a bowl.


112
00:06:10,736 --> 00:06:13,736
And these are defined
per target.


113
00:06:14,186 --> 00:06:16,886
So if your app uses one
set of capabilities,


114
00:06:17,286 --> 00:06:20,416
and your app extension uses
another set, that's fine.


115
00:06:20,896 --> 00:06:25,966
And Xcode has a dedicated editor
for working with capabilities,


116
00:06:26,336 --> 00:06:27,716
called the Capabilities tab.


117
00:06:28,316 --> 00:06:32,366
And the Capabilities tab will
manage your entitlements PLIST


118
00:06:32,596 --> 00:06:34,186
in the configuration details.


119
00:06:34,566 --> 00:06:36,976
So you don't have to visit
the developer website.


120
00:06:37,206 --> 00:06:39,336
You can do it all
from within Xcode.


121
00:06:39,876 --> 00:06:44,576
So those are the things you
need in order to sign your apps.


122
00:06:45,026 --> 00:06:48,066
Now what happens when Xcode
goes to sign your app?


123
00:06:48,366 --> 00:06:50,326
It needs to know which
certificate to use,


124
00:06:50,326 --> 00:06:51,586
and which provision and profile.


125
00:06:52,106 --> 00:06:55,616
The way that works is,
Xcode will build your app.


126
00:06:56,276 --> 00:07:00,066
And then it looks at the list
of certificates on your machine.


127
00:07:00,376 --> 00:07:04,286
And it picks the newest one that
matches your development team.


128
00:07:05,236 --> 00:07:07,866
Xcode then looks at
the list of profiles.


129
00:07:08,356 --> 00:07:11,326
And it picks the newest one
that matches your bundle ID.


130
00:07:11,326 --> 00:07:14,056
And these two things
are brought together.


131
00:07:14,446 --> 00:07:16,776
The profile is embedded
in the app.


132
00:07:17,736 --> 00:07:19,856
And the certificate
is used with Code Sign


133
00:07:20,076 --> 00:07:21,206
to apply the code seal.


134
00:07:21,736 --> 00:07:25,266
So that's a quick
run through of some


135
00:07:25,266 --> 00:07:28,286
of the fundamentals
of signing your apps.


