00:28:44,046 --> 00:28:47,776
So we just saw the new
workflows in Xcode 8


576
00:28:47,776 --> 00:28:50,826
that makes it really easy
and fast to manage signing.


577
00:28:51,886 --> 00:28:54,486
Now I'd like to talk
about some best practices


578
00:28:54,686 --> 00:28:56,806
for managing signing
in your projects.


579
00:28:58,296 --> 00:29:00,836
The first thing is,
use automatic.


580
00:29:01,186 --> 00:29:04,756
Automatic is designed to make
your life as easy as possible.


581
00:29:05,296 --> 00:29:07,436
And it works great


582
00:29:07,436 --> 00:29:10,756
with individual developers,
or large teams.


583
00:29:11,166 --> 00:29:14,526
So you should add all of the
developers that work on your app


584
00:29:14,966 --> 00:29:16,766
to your development team.


585
00:29:17,456 --> 00:29:21,246
You should use the Capabilities
tab to manage entitlements.


586
00:29:21,496 --> 00:29:23,716
So you can avoid visiting
the developer website


587
00:29:23,826 --> 00:29:26,426
to configure things
like iCloud containers.


588
00:29:27,136 --> 00:29:33,296
If you use customized signing,
don't set code sign identity.


589
00:29:33,846 --> 00:29:36,036
You have a specific
signing certificate


590
00:29:36,146 --> 00:29:37,756
that is linked to your account.


591
00:29:38,306 --> 00:29:41,266
So if you set this to your
particular signing cert


592
00:29:41,486 --> 00:29:43,186
and someone else
pulls your project,


593
00:29:43,746 --> 00:29:44,946
they won't be able to build.


594
00:29:45,356 --> 00:29:47,516
So you should leave that
with the default value.


595
00:29:48,856 --> 00:29:51,616
Instead of visiting the
Build Settings Editor,


596
00:29:51,836 --> 00:29:53,116
you should use the new UI


597
00:29:53,296 --> 00:29:55,456
in the General tab
of the Target Editor.


598
00:29:56,186 --> 00:29:59,936
This allows you to see more
information about the profile.


599
00:29:59,936 --> 00:30:04,736
And it also correctly sets
the profile specifier by name,


600
00:30:05,016 --> 00:30:07,096
so you can avoid churn
in your projects.


601
00:30:07,656 --> 00:30:11,306
You should also use
the Capabilities tab


602
00:30:11,506 --> 00:30:14,566
in Customized Signing Mode to
manage your entitlements PLIST.


603
00:30:15,036 --> 00:30:19,526
And if you use development
signing for all


604
00:30:19,526 --> 00:30:23,276
of your project's configuration,
you should try out automatic.


605
00:30:23,836 --> 00:30:26,606
When you get back to your
Mac, go check that checkbox


606
00:30:26,606 --> 00:30:30,966
in the target editor
and try it out.


607
00:30:31,726 --> 00:30:34,436
When it comes to
distributing your app,


608
00:30:34,436 --> 00:30:37,306
Xcode has a dedicated
workflow for this.


609
00:30:37,646 --> 00:30:40,576
And it's based around
building an archive.


610
00:30:42,246 --> 00:30:44,396
Archives contain a
copy of your app.


611
00:30:45,736 --> 00:30:47,306
And it's important to note


612
00:30:47,306 --> 00:30:49,306
that you should use
development signing.


613
00:30:50,316 --> 00:30:53,426
If you sign your app with
a distribution certificate,


614
00:30:53,826 --> 00:30:56,296
you won't be able to
test the exact bits


615
00:30:56,296 --> 00:30:57,666
that you were trying to develop.


616
00:30:58,386 --> 00:31:00,746
So this should be
development signed.


617
00:31:01,376 --> 00:31:03,636
And when it comes time
to distribute that,


618
00:31:03,936 --> 00:31:05,276
when you use the organizer,


619
00:31:05,626 --> 00:31:09,696
Xcode will resign the app using
your development certificate


620
00:31:09,826 --> 00:31:11,466
and provisioning profiles.


621
00:31:12,356 --> 00:31:14,656
And if you clicked
Upload it will go straight


622
00:31:14,656 --> 00:31:15,436
to iTunes connect.


623
00:31:16,206 --> 00:31:20,406
Or if you clicked Export,
you'll get an IPA file or an app


624
00:31:20,506 --> 00:31:22,316
that has been distribution
signed.


625
00:31:23,456 --> 00:31:28,866
So that's the best practice
for distributing your content.


